{"title":"Fiend","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Fiend","type":"markdown","data":"***Version [0.26](/0.26 \"0.26\")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 \"0.32\") of Crawl.*\n\n**Fiends** are three specific [greater demons](/Greater_demon \"Greater demon\"), usually found only in the later parts of the game. All of them are able to inflict [torment](/Torment \"Torment\") as well as dangerous direct-damage spells, making them some of the deadliest end-game monsters. They are:\n\n- 1 [![Brimstone Fiend.png](/images/9/93/Brimstone_Fiend.png)](/File:Brimstone_Fiend.png) **[Brimstone Fiend](/Brimstone_Fiend \"Brimstone Fiend\")**s, who also throw [Damnation](/Damnation \"Damnation\"). Previously they were simply called **Fiends**.\n- 1 [![Ice Fiend.png](/images/a/a8/Ice_Fiend.png)](/File:Ice_Fiend.png) **[Ice Fiend](/Ice_Fiend \"Ice Fiend\")**s, who throw [bolts of cold](/Bolt_of_cold \"Bolt of cold\") and have a cold-branded melee attack.\n- 1 [![Tzitzimitl.png](/images/0/02/Tzitzimitl.png)](/File:Tzitzimitl.png) **[Tzitzimimeh](/Tzitzimitl \"Tzitzimitl\")** (previously known as **Shadow Fiends**), who throw bolts of cold and [draining](/Bolt_of_draining \"Bolt of draining\"). They also cast [Dispel Undead Range](/Dispel_Undead_Range \"Dispel Undead Range\") and can [drain speed](/Slow \"Slow\") and the player's [HP](/HP \"HP\") with their melee attacks.\n\n## History\n\nThese monsters have bedeviled late-game characters since very early versions of *Crawl*. There used to be another type of fiend, however: [pit fiends](/Pit_fiend \"Pit fiend\"), which were similar to Brimstone Fiends but slower and stronger. They were reworked to become [Hell Sentinels](/Hell_Sentinel \"Hell Sentinel\"), gaining normal speed, even more resilience, and nasty Earth conjurations in addition to Damnation, but they lost their ability to torment.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charse