\";\n</script>\n<div class=\"adsense\">\n\t\t<script type=\"text/javascript\"><!--\n\t\tgoogle_ad_client = \"ca-pub-7088061744296615\";\n\t\t/* CrawlWiki skyscraper */\n\t\tgoogle_ad_slot = \"8196155564\";\n\t\tgoogle_ad_width = 160;\n\t\tgoogle_ad_height = 600;\n-->\n</script>\n<script type=\"text/javascript\"\nsrc=\"http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js\">\n</script>\n</div>\n\n\t\t\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n</div>\n\t\t\t<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Fiend</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From CrawlWiki</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\" class=\"mw-jump\">\n\t\t\t\t\tJump to:\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#mw-head\">navigation</a>, \t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#p-search\">search</a>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div style=\"border: 1px solid #f90; background-color: #fc6; border-left: 15px solid #f90; margin-bottom: 20px; width: 100%; padding: 4px 10px; line-height: 1.1em; width: auto;\"><i><b>Version <a href=\"/0.26\" title=\"0.26\">0.26</a></b>: This article <b>may not be</b> up to date for the <a href=\"/0.32\" title=\"0.32\">latest stable release</a> of Crawl.</i></div>\n<p><b>Fiends</b> are three specific <a href=\"/Greater_demon\" title=\"Greater demon\">greater demons</a>, usually found only in the later parts of the game. All of them are able to inflict <a href=\"/Torment\" title=\"Torment\">torment</a> as well as dangerous direct-damage spells, making them some of the deadliest end-game monsters. They are:\n</p>\n<ul><li> <span class=\"nhsym\" style=\"color: #ff5555\">1</span> <a href=\"/File:Brimstone_Fiend.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Brimstone Fiend.png\" src=\"/images/9/93/Brimstone_Fiend.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/Brimstone_Fiend\" title=\"Brimstone Fiend\">Brimstone Fiend</a></b>s, who also throw <a href=\"/Damnation\" title=\"Damnation\">Damnation</a>. Previously they were simply called <b>Fiends</b>.</li>\n<li> <span class=\"nhsym clr-white\">1</span> <a href=\"/File:Ice_Fiend.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Ice Fiend.png\" src=\"/images/a/a8/Ice_Fiend.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/Ice_Fiend\" title=\"Ice Fiend\">Ice Fiend</a></b>s, who throw <a href=\"/Bolt_of_cold\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bolt of cold\">bolts of cold</a> and have a cold-branded melee attack.</li>\n<li> <span class=\"nhsym clr-magenta\">1</span> <a href=\"/File:Tzitzimitl.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Tzitzimitl.png\" src=\"/images/0/02/Tzitzimitl.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" /></a> <b><a href=\"/Tzitzimitl\" title=\"Tzitzimitl\">Tzitzimimeh</a></b> (previously known as <b>Shadow Fiends</b>), who throw bolts of cold and <a href=\"/Bolt_of_draining\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bolt of draining\">draining</a>. They also cast <a href=\"/Dispel_Undead_Range\" title=\"Dispel Undead Range\">Dispel Undead Range</a> and can <a href=\"/Slow\" title=\"Slow\">drain speed</a> and the player's <a href=\"/HP\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"HP\">HP</a> with their melee attacks.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span></h2>\n<p>These monsters have bedeviled late-game characters since very early versions of <i>Crawl</i>. There used to be another type of fiend, however: <a href=\"/Pit_fiend\" title=\"Pit fiend\">pit fiends</a>, which were similar to Brimstone Fiends but slower and stronger. They were reworked to become <a href=\"/Hell_Sentinel\" title=\"Hell Sentinel\">Hell Sentinels</a>, gaining normal speed, even more resilience, and nasty Earth conjurations in addition to Damnation, but they lost their ability to torment.\n</p>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240916222940\nCache expiry: 86400\n